title: Tunisia: Tunisia, Congo Agree to Launch Air Service in 2016
text:
Tunisia, Congo Agree to Launch Air Service in 2016 Tagged: Egypt: Suicide Bombing 'Thwarted' in North Sinai, Assailant Killed - Interior Ministry 
Tunis — Tunisia and Congo, Monday, signed an agreement on the launch of an air service between the two countries from 2016. 
The agreement, signed at a meeting held in Tunis under the chairmanship of Minister of Transport Mahmoud Ben Romdhane, in the presence of the Director of Congo's Air Transport, the CEO of Tunisair and the Director General of Civil Aviation, also establishes a bilateral co-operation programme in the technical fields, training and exchange of expertise. 
The agreement is part of the implementation of the strategy to strengthen partnership with African countries and Tunisia
